This paper focuses on training statistical models for dependency parsing with partial annotation, which is a problem in natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes two different approaches for training the models, which involves optimization and machine learning techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the effectiveness of the proposed approaches and compares them to existing methods, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper uses experiments on a dataset, which could potentially fall under cs.CV (Computer Vision) as well.
